# UI Component Rules

This project uses **shadcn/ui exclusively** for all UI elements. No custom UI components may be created under any circumstances.

## Rules

- **Only shadcn/ui components** are permitted for all UI — buttons, inputs, dialogs, cards, forms, etc.
- **Never** create custom-styled components, raw HTML elements with inline styles, or hand-rolled CSS classes for UI purposes.
- If shadcn/ui is not initialized, run: `npx shadcn@latest init`
- If a required component is not yet installed, add it before use. Example: `npx shadcn@latest add button`

## Dark Mode Theme

The project theme is **dark mode**. All components must respect dark mode contrast rules:

- **Never** use dark text on dark backgrounds — always ensure sufficient contrast.
- Text on dark backgrounds must use light colors (e.g. `text-white`, `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`).
- Avoid Tailwind classes like `text-gray-800`, `text-black`, or `text-zinc-900` on dark surfaces.
- When using shadcn/ui components, rely on their CSS variable-based tokens (`foreground`, `muted-foreground`, `card-foreground`, etc.) which are dark-mode-aware.
- Always verify new UI against a dark background — no component should be invisible or unreadable due to low contrast.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — uses theme-aware tokens, readable on dark backgrounds
<p className="text-foreground">Visible text</p>
<p className="text-muted-foreground">Secondary text</p>

// ❌ BAD — dark text invisible on dark backgrounds
<p className="text-gray-900">Hidden text</p>
<p className="text-black">Hidden text</p>
```

## Clerk Authentication UI

- All Clerk sign-in and sign-up **trigger buttons must use the shadcn/ui `<Button>` component** — never Clerk's default styled buttons.
- Clerk must be configured to launch sign-in and sign-up via a **modal**, not a redirect to a separate page.
- Use Clerk's `<SignInButton mode="modal">` and `<SignUpButton mode="modal">` props to enable modal behavior.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — shadcn/ui Button triggers Clerk modal
import { SignInButton, SignUpButton } from "@clerk/nextjs";
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";

<SignInButton mode="modal">
  <Button variant="outline">Sign In</Button>
</SignInButton>

<SignUpButton mode="modal">
  <Button>Sign Up</Button>
</SignUpButton>
```

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — custom button or Clerk default button, or redirect mode
<SignInButton /> // Clerk's default styled button
<button onClick={...}>Sign In</button> // raw HTML element
<SignInButton mode="redirect"> // redirect instead of modal
  <Button>Sign In</Button>
</SignInButton>
```
